WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.580
Genesis, chapters 46 through 50, from the Holy Bible, King James Version.

00:31.060 --> 00:36.280
And Israel took his journey with all that he had, and came to Beersheba, and offered

00:36.280 --> 00:39.380
sacrifices unto the God of his father, Isaac.

00:40.440 --> 00:45.980
And God spake unto Israel in the visions of the night, and said, Jacob, Jacob.

00:46.360 --> 00:48.320
And he said, Here am I.

00:48.740 --> 00:52.100
And he said, I am God, the God of thy father.

00:52.500 --> 00:57.280
Fear not to go down into Egypt, for I will there make of thee a great nation.

00:57.640 --> 01:03.320
I will go down with thee into Egypt, and I will also surely bring thee up again, and

01:03.320 --> 01:06.100
Joseph shall put his hand upon thine eyes.

01:07.040 --> 01:12.280
And Jacob rose up from Beersheba, and the sons of Israel carried Jacob their father,

01:12.520 --> 01:17.340
and their little ones, and their wives, in the wagons which Pharaoh had sent to carry

01:17.340 --> 01:17.800
him.

01:18.660 --> 01:23.240
And they took their cattle, and their goods, which they had gotten in the land of Canaan,

01:23.520 --> 01:29.760
and came into Egypt, Jacob and all his seed with him, his sons and his sons' sons with

01:29.760 --> 01:35.220
him, his daughters and his sons' daughters, and all his seed brought he with him into

01:35.220 --> 01:35.780
Egypt.

01:36.960 --> 01:42.100
And these are the names of the children of Israel which came into Egypt, Jacob and his

01:42.100 --> 01:49.440
sons, Reuben, Jacob's first born, and the sons of Reuben, Hainach and Falu and Hezren

01:49.440 --> 01:58.200
and Carmi, and the sons of Simeon, Jemuel and Jamin and Ohad and Jakin and Zohar and

02:01.140 --> 02:09.600
and the sons of Levi, Gershon, Kohath and Marari, and the sons of Judah, Ur and Onan

02:09.600 --> 02:17.080
and Shelah and Phares and Zirah, but Ur and Onan died in the land of Canaan, and the sons

02:17.080 --> 02:25.720
of Phares were Hezren and Hamel, and the sons of Issachar, Tola and Fuva and Job and Shimron,

02:26.330 --> 02:33.460
and the sons of Zebulon, Seiread and Elan and Jahlil. These be the sons of Leah which

02:33.460 --> 02:39.300
she bear unto Jacob and Paedon Aram with his daughter Dinah, all the souls of his sons

02:39.300 --> 02:41.780
and his daughters were thirty and three.

02:43.260 --> 02:55.300
And the sons of Gad, Ziphion and Haggai, Shunai and Esben, Eri and Erodai and Erili, and the

02:58.020 --> 03:09.340
sons of Biraeah, Heber and Malkiel. These are the sons of Zilpah whom Laban gave to

03:09.340 --> 03:16.880
Leah his daughter and these she bear unto Jacob even sixteen souls. The sons of Rachel

03:16.880 --> 03:23.940
Jacob's wife, Joseph and Benjamin, and unto Joseph in the land of Egypt were born Manasseh

03:23.940 --> 03:30.820
and Ephraim which Azaneth the daughter of Potipharah, priest of An, bear unto him. And

03:30.820 --> 03:39.660
the sons of Benjamin were Bela and Beker and Ashbel, Gira and Naaman, Ehai and Rosh, Muppim

03:39.660 --> 03:46.260
and Huppim and Ard. These are the sons of Rachel which were born to Jacob, all the souls

03:46.260 --> 03:47.140
were fourteen.

03:48.080 --> 03:56.560
And the sons of Dan, Hushim, and the sons of Naphtali, Jaziel and Gunai and Jezer and

03:56.560 --> 04:02.600
Shilam. These are the sons of Bilhah which Laban gave unto Rachel his daughter and she

04:02.600 --> 04:09.060
bear these unto Jacob. All the souls were seven. All the souls that came with Jacob

04:09.060 --> 04:15.680
into Egypt which came out of his loins besides Jacob's son's wives, all the souls were threescore

04:15.680 --> 04:22.180
and six. And the sons of Joseph which were born him in Egypt were two souls. All the

04:22.180 --> 04:29.000
souls of the house of Jacob which came into Egypt were threescore and ten. And he sent

04:29.000 --> 04:34.660
Judah before him unto Joseph to direct his face unto Goshen and they came into the land

04:34.660 --> 04:41.540
of Goshen. And Joseph made ready his chariot and went up to meet Israel his father to Goshen

04:41.540 --> 04:48.000
and presented himself unto him and he fell on his neck and wept on his neck a good while.

04:49.400 --> 04:55.740
And Israel said unto Joseph, Now let me die since I have seen thy face because thou art

04:55.740 --> 05:02.560
yet alive. And Joseph said unto his brethren and unto his father's house, I will go up

05:02.560 --> 05:08.120
and show Pharaoh and say unto him, My brethren and my father's house which were in the land

05:08.120 --> 05:13.440
of Canaan are come unto me. And the men are shepherds for their trade hath been to feed

05:13.440 --> 05:19.040
cattle and they have brought their flocks and their herds and all that they have. And

05:19.040 --> 05:24.340
it shall come to pass when Pharaoh shall call you and shall say, What is your occupation?

05:24.780 --> 05:29.980
That ye shall say, Thy servant's trade hath been about cattle from our youth even until

05:29.980 --> 05:36.400
now, both we and also our fathers. That ye may dwell in the land of Goshen for every

05:36.400 --> 05:39.240
shepherd is an abomination unto the Egyptians.

05:41.180 --> 05:48.480
Chapter 47 Then Joseph came and told Pharaoh and said, My father and my brethren and their

05:48.480 --> 05:54.300
flocks and their herds and all that they have are come out of the land of Canaan and behold

05:54.300 --> 06:00.780
they are in the land of Goshen. And he took some of his brethren, even five men, and presented

06:00.780 --> 06:07.020
them unto Pharaoh. And Pharaoh said unto his brethren, What is your occupation? And

06:07.020 --> 06:14.840
they said unto Pharaoh, Thy servants are shepherds, both we and also our fathers. They said moreover

06:14.840 --> 06:20.920
unto Pharaoh, For to sojourn in the land are we come, for thy servants have no pasture

06:20.920 --> 06:26.900
for their flocks, for the famine is sore in the land of Canaan. Now therefore we pray

06:26.900 --> 06:30.300
thee, let thy servants dwell in the land of Goshen.

06:31.240 --> 06:37.040
And Pharaoh spake unto Joseph, saying, Thy father and thy brethren are come unto thee,

06:37.380 --> 06:42.960
the land of Egypt is before thee, in the best of the land make thy father and brethren to

06:42.960 --> 06:48.820
dwell, in the land of Goshen let them dwell, and if thou knowest any men of activity among

06:48.820 --> 06:51.480
them, then make them rulers over my cattle.

06:52.480 --> 06:58.200
And Joseph brought in Jacob his father, and set him before Pharaoh, and Jacob blessed

06:58.200 --> 07:02.920
Pharaoh. And Pharaoh said unto Jacob, How old art thou?

07:03.860 --> 07:09.400
And Jacob said unto Pharaoh, The days of the years of my pilgrimage are an hundred and

07:09.400 --> 07:15.500
thirty years. Few and evil have the days of the years of my life been, and have not attained

07:15.500 --> 07:20.500
unto the days of the years of the life of my fathers in the days of their pilgrimage.

07:21.840 --> 07:25.680
And Jacob blessed Pharaoh, and went out from before Pharaoh.

07:27.320 --> 07:32.060
And Joseph placed his father and his brethren, and gave them a possession in the land of

07:32.060 --> 07:37.840
Egypt, in the best of the land, in the land of Ramesses, as Pharaoh had commanded.

07:38.860 --> 07:44.360
And Joseph nourished his father and his brethren, and all his father's household with bread,

07:44.360 --> 07:49.780
according to their families. And there was no bread in all the land, for

07:49.780 --> 07:54.860
the famine was very sore, so that the land of Egypt and all the land of Canaan fainted

07:54.860 --> 08:00.460
by reason of the famine. And Joseph gathered up all the money that was found in the land

08:00.460 --> 08:05.800
of Egypt and in the land of Canaan, for the corn which they bought, and Joseph brought

08:05.800 --> 08:12.100
the money into Pharaoh's house. And when money failed in the land of Egypt and in the land

08:12.100 --> 08:18.360
of Canaan, all the Egyptians came unto Joseph, and said, Give us bread, for why should we

08:18.360 --> 08:25.300
die in thy presence? for the money faileth. And Joseph said, Give your cattle, and I will

08:25.300 --> 08:31.200
give you for your cattle, if money fail. And they brought their cattle unto Joseph, and

08:31.200 --> 08:36.260
Joseph gave them bread in exchange for horses, and for the flocks, and for the cattle of

08:36.260 --> 08:41.880
the herds, and for the asses, and he fed them with bread for all their cattle for that year.

08:43.180 --> 08:48.660
When that year was ended, they came unto him the second year, and said unto him, We will

08:48.660 --> 08:54.740
not hide it from my Lord, how that our money is spent. My Lord also hath our herds of cattle.

08:55.280 --> 09:01.460
There is not aught left in the sight of my Lord, but our bodies and our lands. Wherefore

09:01.460 --> 09:08.120
shall we die before thine eyes, both we and our land? Buy us and our land for bread, and

09:08.120 --> 09:14.220
we and our land will be servants unto Pharaoh. And give us seed that we may live and not

09:14.220 --> 09:20.760
die, that the land be not desolate. And Joseph bought all the land of Egypt for Pharaoh,

09:21.180 --> 09:26.880
for the Egyptians sold every man his field because the famine prevailed over them, so

09:26.880 --> 09:33.120
the land became Pharaoh's. And as for the people, he removed them to cities from one

09:33.120 --> 09:39.240
end of the borders of Egypt even to the other end thereof. Only the land of the priests

09:39.240 --> 09:44.840
bought he not, for the priests had a portion assigned them of Pharaoh, and did eat their

09:44.840 --> 09:51.720
portion which Pharaoh gave them, wherefore they sold not their lands. Then Joseph said

09:51.720 --> 09:58.100
unto the people, Behold, I have bought you this day and your land for Pharaoh. Lo, here

09:58.100 --> 10:03.560
is seed for you, and ye shall sow the land. And it shall come to pass in the increase

10:03.560 --> 10:09.740
that ye shall give the fifth part unto Pharaoh, and four parts shall be your own, for seed

10:09.740 --> 10:15.180
of the field, and for your food, and for them of your households, and for food for your

10:15.180 --> 10:21.480
little ones. And they said, Thou hast saved our lives. Let us find grace in the sight

10:21.480 --> 10:28.340
of my Lord, and we will be Pharaoh's servants. And Joseph made it a law over the land of

10:28.340 --> 10:33.900
Egypt unto this day that Pharaoh should have the fifth part, except the land of the priests

10:33.900 --> 10:41.100
only, which became not Pharaoh's. And Israel dwelt in the land of Egypt in the country

10:41.100 --> 10:48.260
of Goshen, and they had possessions therein, and grew and multiplied exceedingly. And Jacob

10:48.260 --> 10:54.280
lived in the land of Egypt seventeen years, so the whole age of Jacob was an hundred forty

10:54.280 --> 11:01.260
and seven years. And the time drew nigh that Israel must die, and he called his son Joseph,

11:01.400 --> 11:07.440
and said unto him, If now I have found grace in thy sight, put, I pray thee, thy hand under

11:07.440 --> 11:14.440
my thigh, and deal kindly and truly with me. Bury me not, I pray thee, in Egypt. But I

11:14.440 --> 11:20.260
will lie with my fathers, and thou shalt carry me out of Egypt, and bury me in their burying

11:20.260 --> 11:27.520
place. And he said, I will do as thou hast said. And he said, Swear unto me. And he

11:27.520 --> 11:32.060
swear unto him. And Israel bowed himself upon the bed's head.

11:34.500 --> 11:39.100
CHAPTER 48 And it came to pass after these things that

11:39.100 --> 11:45.980
one told Joseph, Behold, thy father is sick. And he took with him his two sons Manasseh

11:45.980 --> 11:53.080
and Ephraim. And one told Jacob, and said, Behold, thy son Joseph cometh unto thee. And

11:53.080 --> 11:55.940
Israel strengthened himself and sat upon the bed.

11:57.320 --> 12:04.020
And Jacob said unto Joseph, God Almighty appeared unto me at Luz in the land of Canaan, and

12:04.020 --> 12:10.020
blessed me, and said unto me, Behold, I will make thee fruitful and multiply thee, and

12:10.020 --> 12:15.100
I will make of thee a multitude of people, and will give this land to thy seed after

12:15.100 --> 12:21.920
thee for an everlasting possession. And now thy two sons Ephraim and Manasseh,

12:21.920 --> 12:27.560
which were born unto thee in the land of Egypt before I came unto thee into Egypt, are mine.

12:28.040 --> 12:34.200
As Reuben and Simeon they shall be mine. And thy issue, which thou begettest after them,

12:34.460 --> 12:39.180
shall be thine, and shall be called after the name of their brethren and their inheritance.

12:40.360 --> 12:46.500
And as for me, when I came from Paden, Rachel died by me in the land of Canaan in the way,

12:46.840 --> 12:52.220
when yet there was but a little way to come unto Ephrath, and I buried her there in the

12:52.220 --> 12:59.260
way of Ephrath, the same as Bethlehem. And Israel beheld Joseph's sons, and said,

12:59.380 --> 13:05.840
Who were these? And Joseph said unto his father, They are my sons, whom God hath given me in

13:05.840 --> 13:11.640
this place. And he said, Bring them, I pray thee, unto me, and I will bless them.

13:12.660 --> 13:18.200
Now the eyes of Israel were dim for age, so that he could not see, and he brought them

13:18.200 --> 13:25.260
near unto him, and he kissed them, and embraced them. And Israel said unto Joseph, I had not

13:25.260 --> 13:32.420
thought to see thy face, and lo, God hath showed me also thy seed. And Joseph brought

13:32.420 --> 13:39.140
them out from between his knees, and he bowed himself with his face to the earth. And Joseph

13:39.140 --> 13:44.880
took them both, Ephraim in his right hand toward Israel's left hand, and Manasseh in

13:44.880 --> 13:50.940
his left hand toward Israel's right hand, and brought them near unto him. And Israel

13:50.940 --> 13:55.460
stretched out his right hand, and laid it upon Ephraim's head, who was the younger,

13:55.820 --> 14:01.700
and his left hand upon Manasseh's head, guiding his hands wittingly, for Manasseh was the

14:01.700 --> 14:09.140
first born. And he blessed Joseph, and said, God, before whom my fathers Abraham and Isaac

14:09.140 --> 14:15.760
did walk, the God which fed me all my life long, unto this day, the angel which redeemed

14:15.760 --> 14:21.720
me from all evil, bless the lads, and let my name be named on them, and the name of

14:21.720 --> 14:27.560
my fathers Abraham and Isaac, and let them grow into a multitude in the midst of the

14:27.560 --> 14:33.600
earth. And when Joseph saw that his father laid his right hand upon the head of Ephraim,

14:33.600 --> 14:39.940
it displeased him, and he held up his father's hand to remove it from Ephraim's head unto

14:39.940 --> 14:46.700
Manasseh's head. And Joseph said unto his father, Not so, my father, for this is the

14:46.700 --> 14:53.700
first born, put thy right hand upon his head. And his father refused, and said, I know it,

14:53.700 --> 15:00.780
my son, I know it. He also shall become a people, and he also shall be great. But truly

15:00.780 --> 15:05.840
his younger brother shall be greater than he, and his seed shall become a multitude

15:05.840 --> 15:13.060
of nations. And he blessed them that day, saying, In thee shall Israel bless, saying,

15:13.300 --> 15:21.140
God make thee as Ephraim and as Manasseh, and he set Ephraim before Manasseh. And Israel

15:21.140 --> 15:28.080
said unto Joseph, Behold, I die, but God shall be with you and bring you again unto the land

15:28.080 --> 15:34.460
of your fathers. Moreover, I have given to thee one portion above thy brethren, which

15:34.460 --> 15:38.980
I took out of the hand of the Amorite, with my sword and with my bow.

15:40.900 --> 15:46.480
Chapter 49 And Jacob called unto his sons, and said, Gather

15:46.480 --> 15:52.800
yourselves together, that I may tell you that which shall befall you in the last days. Gather

15:52.800 --> 15:58.580
yourselves together, and hear, ye sons of Jacob, and hearken unto Israel, your father.

16:00.040 --> 16:05.920
Reuben, thou art my first born, my might, and the beginning of my strength, the excellency

16:05.920 --> 16:13.920
of dignity, and the excellency of power. Unstable as water, thou shalt not excel, because thou

16:13.920 --> 16:19.900
wentest up to thy father's bed, then defiledst thou it. He went up to my couch.

16:21.640 --> 16:28.400
Simeon and Levi are brethren, instruments of cruelty are in their habitations. O my

16:28.400 --> 16:34.440
soul, come not thou into their secret, unto their assembly, mine honor, be not thou united,

16:35.020 --> 16:41.480
for in their anger they slew a man, and in their self-will they digged down a wall. Cursed

16:41.480 --> 16:47.200
be their anger, for it was fierce, and their wrath, for it was cruel, I will divide them

16:47.200 --> 16:49.860
in Jacob, and scatter them in Israel.

16:51.860 --> 16:57.260
Judah, thou art he whom thy brethren shall praise, thy hand shall be in the neck of

16:57.260 --> 17:04.200
thine enemies, thy father's children shall bow down before thee. Judah is a lion's whelp.

17:04.580 --> 17:10.960
From the prey, my son, thou art gone up. He stooped down, he couched as a lion, and as

17:10.960 --> 17:18.160
an old lion, who shall rouse him up? The scepter shall not depart from Judah, nor a law-giver

17:18.160 --> 17:24.080
from between his feet, until Shiloh come, and unto him shall the gathering of the people

17:24.080 --> 17:31.240
be. Binding his foal unto the vine, and his asses colt unto the choice-vine, he washed

17:31.240 --> 17:37.540
his garments in wine, and his clothes in the blood of grapes. His eyes shall be red with

17:37.540 --> 17:45.600
wine, and his teeth white with milk. Zebulon shall dwell at the haven of the sea, and he

17:45.600 --> 17:53.080
shall be for an haven of ships, and his border shall be unto Zidon. Issachar is a strong

17:53.080 --> 17:59.520
ass couching down between two burdens, and he saw that rest was good, and the land that

17:59.520 --> 18:06.900
it was pleasant, and bowed his shoulder to bear, and became a servant unto tribute. Dan

18:06.900 --> 18:13.180
shall judge his people as one of the tribes of Israel. Dan shall be a serpent by the way,

18:13.400 --> 18:20.700
an adder in the path, that biteth the horse-heels, so that his rider shall fall backward. I have

18:20.700 --> 18:28.280
waited for thy salvation, O Lord. Gad, a troop shall overcome him, but he shall overcome

18:28.280 --> 18:35.740
at the last. Out of Asher his bread shall be fat, and he shall yield royal deities.

18:37.100 --> 18:45.620
Naphtali is a hind let loose, he giveth goodly words. Joseph is a fruitful bow, even a fruitful

18:45.620 --> 18:51.860
bow by a well, whose branches run over the wall. The archers have sorely grieved him,

18:52.040 --> 18:58.200
and shot at him, and hated him. But his bow abode in strength, and the arms of his hands

18:58.200 --> 19:03.560
were made strong by the hands of the mighty God of Jacob. From thence is the shepherd

19:03.560 --> 19:10.360
the stone of Israel. Even by the God of thy father, who shall help thee, and by the Almighty,

19:10.620 --> 19:15.800
who shall bless thee with blessings of heaven above, blessings of the deep that lieth under,

19:16.180 --> 19:21.600
blessings of the breasts, and of the womb. The blessings of thy father have prevailed

19:21.600 --> 19:27.140
above the blessings of my progenitors, unto the utmost bound of the everlasting hills.

19:27.660 --> 19:32.720
They shall be on the head of Joseph, and on the crown of the head of him that was separate

19:32.720 --> 19:40.040
from his brethren. Benjamin shall raven as a wolf. In the morning he shall devour the

19:40.040 --> 19:47.780
prey, and at night he shall divide the spoil. All these are the twelve tribes of Israel,

19:48.120 --> 19:52.960
and this is it that their fathers spake unto them, and blessed them. Everyone according

19:52.960 --> 19:59.200
to his blessing, he blessed them. And he charged them, and said unto them, I am to be gathered

19:59.200 --> 20:05.000
unto my people. Bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in the field of Ephron the

20:05.000 --> 20:10.920
Hittite, in the cave that is in the field of Machpelah, which is before Mamre, and the

20:10.920 --> 20:16.680
land of Canaan, which Abraham bought with the field of Ephron the Hittite, for a possession

20:16.680 --> 20:23.980
of a burying place. There they buried Abraham, and Sarah his wife. There they buried Isaac

20:23.980 --> 20:30.740
and Rebekah his wife, and there I buried Leah. The purchase of the field, and of the cave

20:30.740 --> 20:37.280
that is therein, was from the children of Heth. And when Jacob had made an end of commanding

20:37.280 --> 20:43.340
his sons, he gathered up his feet into the bed, and yielded up the ghost, and was gathered

20:43.340 --> 20:44.560
unto his people.

20:46.740 --> 20:51.280
CHAPTER 50 And Joseph fell upon his father's face, and

20:51.280 --> 20:57.200
stepped upon him, and kissed him. And Joseph commanded his servants, the physicians, to

20:57.200 --> 21:03.940
embalm his father, and the physicians embalmed Israel. And forty days were fulfilled for

21:03.940 --> 21:09.500
him, for so are fulfilled the days of those which are embalmed, and the Egyptians mourned

21:09.500 --> 21:16.120
for him three score and ten days. And when the days of his mourning were past, Joseph

21:16.120 --> 21:22.080
spake unto the house of Pharaoh, saying, If now I have found grace in your eyes, speak,

21:22.260 --> 21:29.740
I pray you, in the ears of Pharaoh, saying, My father made me swear, saying, Lo, I die,

21:30.140 --> 21:34.900
in my grave which I have digged for me, in the land of Canaan, there shalt thou bury

21:34.900 --> 21:41.900
me. Now therefore let me go up, I pray thee, and bury my father, and I will come again.

21:42.440 --> 21:48.340
And Pharaoh said, Go up, and bury thy father, according as he made thee swear.

21:49.700 --> 21:55.080
And Joseph went up to bury his father, and with him went up all the servants of Pharaoh,

21:55.520 --> 22:00.780
the elders of his house, and all the elders of the land of Egypt, and all the house of

22:00.780 --> 22:06.460
Joseph, and his brethren, and his father's house. Only their little ones, and their flocks,

22:06.460 --> 22:12.760
and their herds, they left in the land of Goshen. And there went up with him both chariots

22:12.760 --> 22:19.220
and horsemen, and it was a very great company. And they came to the threshing floor of Atad,

22:19.480 --> 22:25.300
which is beyond Jordan, and there they mourned with a great and very sore lamentation, and

22:25.300 --> 22:36.440
he made a mourning for his father seven days. And when the inhabitants of the land, the

22:36.440 --> 22:42.980
grievous mourning to the Egyptians, wherefore the name of it was called Abel-Misraim, which

22:42.980 --> 22:49.860
is beyond Jordan. And his sons did unto him according as he commanded them, for his sons

22:49.860 --> 22:55.520
carried him into the land of Canaan, and buried him in the cave of the field of Machpelah,

22:55.780 --> 23:00.760
which Abraham bought with the field for a possession of a burying-place of Ephra on

23:00.760 --> 23:08.340
the Hittite, before Mamre. And Joseph returned into Egypt, he and his brethren, and all that

23:08.340 --> 23:15.040
went up with him, to bury his father, after he had buried his father. And when Joseph's

23:15.040 --> 23:21.180
brethren saw that their father was dead, they said, Joseph will peradventure hate us, and

23:21.180 --> 23:27.080
will certainly requite us all the evil which we did unto him. And they sent a messenger

23:27.080 --> 23:33.640
unto Joseph, saying, Thy father did command before he died, saying, So shall ye say unto

23:33.920 --> 23:39.880
Joseph, Forgive, I pray thee now, the trespass of thy brethren and their sin, for they did

23:39.880 --> 23:45.600
unto thee evil, and now we pray thee, forgive the trespass of the servants of the God of

23:45.600 --> 23:52.620
thy father. And Joseph wept when they spake unto him. And his brethren also went and fell

23:52.620 --> 24:00.100
down before his face, and they said, Behold, we be thy servants. And Joseph said unto them,

24:00.380 --> 24:08.120
Fear not, for am I in the place of God. But as for you ye thought evil against me, but

24:08.120 --> 24:15.020
God meant it unto good, to bring to pass, as it is this day, to save much people alive.

24:15.620 --> 24:22.400
Now therefore fear ye not, I will nourish you and your little ones. And he comforted

24:22.400 --> 24:29.600
them and spake kindly unto them. And Joseph dwelt in Egypt, he and his father's house.

24:30.140 --> 24:36.260
And Joseph lived and a hundred and ten years. And Joseph saw Ephraim's children of the third

24:36.260 --> 24:42.460
generation. The children also of Maker, the son of Manasseh, were brought up upon Joseph's

24:42.460 --> 24:50.020
knees. And Joseph said unto his brethren, I die, and God will surely visit you and bring

24:50.020 --> 24:55.900
you out of this land, unto the land which he sware to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.

24:56.720 --> 25:02.240
And Joseph took an oath of the children of Israel, saying, God will surely visit you,

25:02.380 --> 25:09.180
and he shall carry up my bones from hence. So Joseph died, being a hundred and ten years

25:09.180 --> 25:14.020
old, and they embalmed him, and he was put in a coffin in Egypt.

